    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Response Latency by Branch (p95)",
      "id": 18,
      "description": "Branches: `simple`, `sql_*`, `hybrid` invoke an LLM here. `rag` is a passthrough — the RAG-agent LLM call already happened upstream (see Full RAG Agent Duration); this panel captures only string-formatting + history prefix + final write, so `rag` should be <100ms. If `rag` is high, the bottleneck is upstream (RAG agent) and the metric just inherits the wait. `error`/`simple` paths skip LLM entirely and should be sub-100ms.",
